 in queer ways enables new histories to emerge, intervenes in a troubled present, and gives hope for unexpected futures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aHebrew poetryxWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aHebrew poetry, ModernxHistory and criticism. 0aJewish lesbiansxPoetryxHistory and criticism. 0aJewish poetryxWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aLesbian heroines in literature. 0aLesbianism in literature. 0aLesbians in literature. 0aYiddish poetryxWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aGeneral Interest : Poetry. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Jewish.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847224940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438472249423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438472249/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles